devdoc.author: Ethereum Tag Service <security@ets.xyz>
devdoc.details: ETS Core utilizes Open Zeppelin UUPS upgradability pattern.

drawDown(address).details: Can be called by the account owner or on behalf of someone.Does nothing when there is nothing due to the account.

params._account: Target address that has had accrued ETH and which will receive the ETH.

returns._0: true for enabled, false for disabled.

returns._publisher: Publisher through which the tag took place.
returns._tagger: Address that tagged the NFT asset.
returns._timestamp: When the tagging record took place.

initialize(address,address).details: Replaces contructor function for UUPS Proxy contracts. Called upon first deployment.

params._setting: Boolean, set true for enabled, false for disabled.

params._fee: Value of the fee in WEI.

params._account: Address of the account being queried.

returns._due: Amount of WEI in ETH due to account.

params._accessControls: Address of the access controls contract.

upgradeTo(address).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

accrued.details: Map for holding amount accrued to participant address wallets.

paid.details: Map for holding lifetime amount drawn down from accrued by participants.

permittedNftChainIds.details: Map for holding permitted tagging target chain ids.

taggingCounter.details: Incremental tagging record counter. Used for tagging record ID.

taggingRecords.details: Map of tagging id to tagging record.

target.details: Map of target id to Target embodied by Target struct.

devdoc.title: ETS Core

drawDown(address).notice: Enables anyone to send ETH accrued by an account.

getPermittedNftChainId(uint256).notice: Check if a target chain is permitted for tagging.

getTargetId(string,string).notice: Get a target Id from target type and target uri. TODO: Finish documentation.

platformPercentage().notice: Percentage of tagging fee allocated to ETS.

publisherPercentage().notice: Percentage of tagging fee allocated to Publisher.

remainingPercentage().notice: Percentage of tagging fee allocated to Creator or Owner.

setPermittedNftChainId(uint256,bool).notice: Admin functionality for enabling/disabling target chains.

setTaggingFee(uint256).notice: Sets the fee required to tag an NFT asset.

tagTarget(string,string,string,address,a.notice: Tag a target with an tag string. TODO: Finish documenting.

taggingFee().notice: Fee in ETH Collected by ETS for tagging.

targetType(string).notice: Currently, types are a simple string identifying the target type. eg. "nft", "url". These are set using setTargetType() Obviously, this is a key area to break out into it's own contract/interface logic so service can be extended by 3rd parties.

totalDue(address).notice: Used to check how much ETH has been accrued by an address factoring in amount paid out.

updateAccessControls(address).notice: Admin functionality for updating the access controls.

updatePercentages(uint256,uint256).notice: Admin functionality for updating the percentages.

userdoc.notice: Core tagging contract that enables any online target to be tagged with an ETSTAG token.
